# Copilot Swarm Orchestrator – Planning & Specification Document

> **Scope of This Document**: This is a planning and specification document for a verification-first, multi-agent coordination methodology built on top of **VS Code GitHub Copilot Chat** (including Agent Mode). It describes the system design, agent profiles, orchestration workflow, and quality standards. It does **not** cover implementation code.

> **Platform Note**: As of 2025, GitHub Copilot **Agent Mode** is available in VS Code Stable for all users, and the Copilot CLI exists as a separate background execution environment. This specification targets the **VS Code Chat + Agent Mode** surface, which is the most accessible and interactive starting point. Where the Copilot CLI offers relevant enhancements (e.g. Git worktree isolation), these are noted as optional upgrades, not requirements.

