## 6. The Eight Post-Merge Quality Gates

These gates are fully **deterministic** — they use regex, AST analysis, file scanning, and static thresholds. No AI or LLM is involved, ensuring that results are reproducible and not subject to hallucination.

Gates are implemented as shell scripts or simple Node/Python scripts stored in `.swarm/gates/` and run as a batch after all merges complete.

| # | Gate | What It Checks | Failure Condition |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **1** | Scaffold Leftovers | Scans all source files for `TODO`, `FIXME`, `PLACEHOLDER`, `Lorem ipsum`, `[INSERT`, and similar markers. | Any occurrence found in non-test files. |
| **2** | Duplicate Code Blocks | Detects repeated code blocks longer than 5 lines using a token-hash comparison. | Duplication ratio exceeds the configured threshold (default: any block appearing 3+ times). |
| **3** | Hardcoded Configuration | Flags magic strings, hardcoded URLs, IP addresses, API keys, or passwords in non-example source files. | Any hardcoded value found in a location that should use environment variables or config. |
| **4** | README Drift | Parses setup commands and feature claims in `README.md` and cross-references them against actual scripts in `package.json` / `Makefile` and directories that exist. | A README command references a script that doesn't exist, or a described feature has no corresponding code directory. |
| **5** | Test Isolation | Detects shared mutable state between test cases (e.g. global variables mutated in one test and read in another, missing `beforeEach` resets). | Any test file where test execution order can affect outcomes. |
| **6** | Test Coverage | Reads the coverage report generated by the test runner and validates it against the configured minimum. | Coverage falls below threshold (default: 80% line coverage). |
| **7** | Accessibility Basics | Parses rendered HTML templates and JSX for missing `alt` attributes on `<img>` elements, missing `aria-label` on interactive elements without text, and form inputs without associated labels. | Any required attribute absent from a non-decorative element. |
| **8** | Runtime Smoke Test | Starts the application (or the relevant service) and sends a minimal health-check request (e.g. `GET /health`). | Process exits with a non-zero code, or the health-check request returns a 5xx response. |

**Gate output**: Each gate produces a pass/fail result and, on failure, a list of the specific files and line numbers that caused the failure. All results are written to `.swarm/gate-results/session-<id>.json`.

