### `.github/copilot-instructions.md`

This file is read automatically by VS Code Copilot at the start of every chat session in the workspace. Use it to establish baseline behaviour that applies to all agents — for example:

```markdown
# Project Copilot Instructions

- All code must be TypeScript strict mode with no `any` types.
- Use the `apiClient` from `src/lib/api.ts` for all HTTP calls. Do not use `fetch` directly.
- Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles.
- Every function touching user data must include input validation.
- Before making any change, state which files you will modify and why.
```

