## 10. Limitations & Honest Caveats

| Limitation | Reality |
| :--- | :--- |
| **No automation** | Everything described in this document — branch creation, agent invocation, verification, repair, and merging — is performed manually by the developer. There is no tool that automates this workflow. |
| **Manual parallelism only** | True parallel execution requires opening multiple VS Code windows on separate branches. There is no background scheduling or process orchestration. |
| **Agent mode quota consumption** | Agent mode consumes premium requests that are quota-limited on all plans. Complex sessions with many steps and repair loops can exhaust monthly quotas. Plan accordingly. |
| **Evidence integrity is your responsibility** | The transcripts and git log are only as reliable as the discipline applied. If you accept an agent's claims without running the verification checklist, the evidence trail is meaningless. |
| **Copilot doesn't always commit** | Even when instructed to commit, Agent mode does not always produce a git commit. Always verify with `git log -1` and prompt the agent to commit if it hasn't. |
| **AI can still hallucinate** | The verification layer exists precisely because AI outputs are unreliable. A passing verification checklist reduces but does not eliminate the risk of subtle bugs. Human code review remains essential. |
| **Not an official GitHub product** | This is a community methodology. It is not endorsed by, affiliated with, or supported by GitHub or Microsoft. Copilot's behaviour may change in ways that require prompt adjustments. |

